Credit goes to WunderTech (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qms3ffm8H_4)

On the NAS: Create an NFS share (e.g. Proxmox-Backup-Server) with everyone RW permission and "all_squash" option (in OMV).

Deploy PBS, and run the helper script.
PBS console:
    mkdir -p /mnt/pbs-backups (to create the datastore in)
    mkdir -p /mnt/temp (to mount the NFS share into)
    chown backup:backup /mnt/pbs-backups
    nano /etc/fstab
        192.168.210.245:/Proxmox-Backup-Server /mnt/temp nfs defaults 0 0
    systemctl daemon-reload && mount -a

PBS WebUI:
    Add datastore:
        General tab:
            Name: OMV
            Backing Path: /mnt/pbs-backups
        Prune Options tab:
            Daily: 7
            Wekkly: 4
            Monthly: 2
            (Keep Last: 13)

PBS console:
    cp -R /mnt/pbs-backups/.chunks /mnt/pbs-backups/.lock /mnt/temp
    nano /etc/fstab
        192.168.210.245:/Proxmox-Backup-Server /mnt/pbs-backups nfs defaults 0 0
    systemctl daemon-reload && umount /mnt/temp && mount -a

Restart PBS to check persistency.

Proxmox VE:
    Web UI:
        Datacenter -> Storage -> Add PBS
            ID: PBS (or anything)
            Server: 192.168.210.4
            Username: root@pam
            Password: 